Final file:

```csharp
using System;
using System.Runtime.InteropServices;

public static class NativeCompression
{
    [DllImport("compresslib", EntryPoint = "compress_buffer",
        CallingConvention = CallingConvention.Cdecl, ExactSpelling = true)]
    public static extern int CompressBuffer(
        byte[] input,
        UIntPtr inputLen,
        byte[] output,
        UIntPtr outputLen,
        out UIntPtr bytesWritten);
}
```

Key choices:

- **`EntryPoint`** — maps the C# name `CompressBuffer` to the native `compress_buffer`.
- **`UIntPtr`** for `size_t` — correct width on x86 (32-bit) and safe if later retargeted to x64.
- **`Cdecl`** — standard C calling convention; required on x86 where the default P/Invoke convention is `StdCall`.
